{
  "texts": [
    "When the data packet arrives in NDN node, the node perform a PIT lookup to discover unsatisfied interest associated with the data packet's name.",
    "If there is a request for the data, the cache management policy of NDN node will then decide whether to cache the data that has arrived.",
    "After that it locates the required interface and sends the data to all downstream interfaces (Rehman et al. 2016).",
    "The NDN data packet forwarding procedure is shown in Fig. 5.",
    "When a consumer presents a request for content, first, the NDN router begin by searching the content name in the CS."
  ]
}